# DO_NOT_UNDO — .gitignore
#
# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║  PERMANENT RULE (verified 22-Apr-2026): DO NOT add `.env`, `*.env`,      ║
# ║  `backend/.env`, or `frontend/.env` patterns to this file.               ║
# ║                                                                          ║
# ║  Why: Emergent native deployment REQUIRES both /app/backend/.env and     ║
# ║  /app/frontend/.env to be committed to the repository so the deploy      ║
# ║  pipeline can inject prod values into them. If these files are           ║
# ║  gitignored, the prod build has no REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL / MONGO_URL /   ║
# ║  Google OAuth client ID, and Google Sign-In breaks with "Network Error"  ║
# ║  on the prod domain (this has happened 5+ times — see CHANGELOG 22-Apr). ║
# ║                                                                          ║
# ║  Safe alternatives already in place:                                     ║
# ║   • Emergent's vault stores the actual secret values, not this repo.     ║
# ║   • Real secrets never appear in source code (all read from os.environ). ║
# ║   • `.env.example` template files ARE ignored (see below).               ║
# ║   • `memory/test_credentials.md` is ignored (see below).                 ║
# ║                                                                          ║
# ║  If a secret-scanner blocks a push, fix the leaked secret — do NOT       ║
# ║  re-ignore the .env files.                                               ║
# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
#
# Dependencies
node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/

# Build output
frontend/build/
dist/
*.whl

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Logs
*.log

# Credential files (NEVER commit secrets). NOTE: .env files intentionally NOT
# listed here — Emergent's native deployment pipeline REQUIRES backend/.env
# and frontend/.env to be committed so the deploy step can inject production
# values into them. The actual secret values live in Emergent's vault.
credentials.json
*.pem
*.key
.credentials
memory/test_credentials.md
/memory/test_credentials.md

# .env.example template files only — NEVER ignore real .env files.
.env.example

# Capacitor
frontend/android/
frontend/ios/

# Coverage
coverage/
htmlcov/
.coverage

# Misc
*.bak
*.tmp

# Webpack cache
frontend/node_modules/.cache/

# Test reports and iteration logs (may contain secrets)
test_reports/
backend/tests/test_google_oauth_iteration*.py
backend/tests/test_security_fixes_iteration*.py
frontend/node_modules/.cache/default-development/25.pack
frontend/node_modules/.cache/default-development/32.pack
frontend/node_modules/.cache/default-development/27.pack
-e 
